                        <bindingDesc>
                            <binding contemporary="true" xml:id="binding">
                              <p>The sewing has been repaired. However, most part of the binding is likely contemporary to the manuscript content.</p>
                              <decoNote xml:id="b1" type="bindingMaterial">
                                The book is bound in <material key="wood">wooden</material> boards, fully covered with reddish-brown blind-tooled <material
                                key="leather">leather</material>.
                              </decoNote>
                              <decoNote xml:id="b2" type="Boards">
                                The boards are slightly larger than the size of the bookblock.
                              </decoNote>
                              <decoNote xml:id="b3" type="Cover" color="reddish-brown">
                                Full reddish-brown blind-tooled leather cover. The turn-ins have been trimmed out and at the corners they form butt mitres.
                                The external surfaces of the cover show a fine blind-tooled decoration.
                                The decoration consists of seven concentric frames surrounding a central rectangular panel featuring a Latin cross.
                                Frames composed by the repetition of single tools, enclosed between <term key="tripleStraightLine">triple straight lines</term>,
                                alternate with empty ones.
                                Proceeding from the outer to the inner frame, the repeating decoration motifs are <term key="crissCross">criss-cross</term>, <term key="XForm">double X-forms</term>,
                                <term key="wavyLine">wavy lines</term> and <term key="curveStrapwork">curve strapwork</term> elements.
                                <term key="straightStrapwork">straight strapwork</term> elements.
                                The cross is formed by <term key="XForm">X-form</term> motifs between triple straight lines.
                                At the ends of the arms of the cross there are pairs of <term key="crescent">crescents</term> disposed to resemble a corniform motif,
                                and three <term key="doubleCircle">double circles</term>. Triple straight lines divide the area around the cross in four panels
                                outlining the shape of the cross.
                                Double circles are also stamped at the intersection of the triple straight lines.
                                On the spine, triple straight lines intersect, forming a diamond pattern.
                              </decoNote>
                              <decoNote xml:id="b4" type="Endbands" color="brown">
                                Brown <term type="slit-braid">slit-braid</term> endbands.
                              </decoNote>
                              <decoNote xml:id="b5" type="SewingStations">4</decoNote>
                              <decoNote xml:id="b6">
                                Chainstitch sewing on four sewing stations (two pairs); periodic fold pattern; Z-plied threads.
                                Between each pair of sewing stations there are two lengths.
                              </decoNote>
                              <decoNote xml:id="b7" type="Spine">
                                The spine is formed by two overlapping layers of leather. The endbands are sewn through the first layer so that
                                the tie-downs are hidden under the second layer.
                              </decoNote>
                            </binding>
                        </bindingDesc>

